<h2 id="capo-4th-fret">Capo 4th fret</h2>

<p>Put a capo on the 4th fret to be able to play along with the album version of this song while using these common &amp; easy-to-play open chords.</p>

<h2 id="chords-used">Chords used</h2>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>E —–—0–––––––––––––––––––––––
B —–—1––––0––––1–––––––––––––   Right thumb plays bass note of each chord.
G —–—0––––0––––2––––0––––2–––
D —–—–––––0––––2––––2––––3–––   Right index, middle, &amp; ring play highest
A —–—3–––––––––0––––2––––3–––         three strings of each chord.
E —–—–––––3–––––––––0––––1–––
     C    G    Am   Em   F
</code></pre></div></div>

